Relax /find threshold: strict 0.85 first, then fall back to 0.50 candidates

The 0.85 strict threshold returned 0 papers for vague queries like
'Holiday hedging in academic writing' (real user query in the last
GHA run, 196 raw papers but 0 above 0.85 because the query is too
general). Now /find first tries the strict 0.85 (the 'verified'
tier), and if nothing matches, falls back to 0.50 (the 'candidates'
tier, flagged as uncertain). User always gets a result.